Police in Keiyo North police pursuing a suspected illicit dealer selling alcohol to tourists and children in Iten.The brewer has devised cunning ways of selling liquor at Tirinya near a picturesque view point. Domestic and foreign tourists throng the view point to watch the expansive and breathtaking Kerio Valley.The brewer is suspected to be selling alcohol to underage children when they visit the site at the weekends. Keiyo North police boss Mwenda Meme said the brewer uses a cave near the view point to avoid being spotted by security agencies. Meme said the suspect has a ferocious dog that prevents anyone, including the police, from getting into his ‘brewing’.